<subSubSection pageId="3" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,417,694]" pageId="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,489,514]" pageId="3">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species was described originally in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Germar" authorityYear="1817" box="[779,944,489,514]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Trachyphloeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[779,944,489,514]" italics="true" pageId="3">Trachyphloeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Seidlitz" box="[1007,1176,489,514]" pageId="3" refString="Seidlitz, G. (1868) Die Otiorhynchiden s. str. nach den morphologischen Verwandtschaftsverhaltnissen ihres Hautscelet's vergleichend dargestellt. Berliner Entomologische Zeitschrift, 12, i - iv, 1 - 153." type="journal article" year="1868">Seidlitz (1868)</bibRefCitation>
synonymised its name with 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Seidlitz" authorityYear="1868" box="[208,365,525,550]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Trachyphloeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spathulatus">
<emphasis box="[208,365,525,550]" italics="true" pageId="3">T. spathulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, without examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[690,738,526,550]" pageId="3">type</typeStatus>
material. He interpreted the differences in the antennae of the two species as sexual dimorphism and considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Borovec &amp; Oberprieler" authorityYear="2013" box="[741,884,561,585]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Afrophloeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="squamifer">
<emphasis box="[741,884,561,585]" italics="true" pageId="3">T. squamifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be the female of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Seidlitz" authorityYear="1868" box="[1130,1291,561,586]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Trachyphloeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spathulatus">
<emphasis box="[1130,1291,561,586]" italics="true" pageId="3">T. spathulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Borovec" pageId="3" refString="Borovec, R. &amp; Oberprieler, R. G. (2013) Afrophloeus, a new genus of African weevils of the tribe Embrithini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Entiminae), with description of a new species and notes on the composition of Embrithini. Zootaxa, 3693 (3), 365 - 378. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3693.3.7" type="journal article" year="2013">Borovec &amp; Oberprieler (2013)</bibRefCitation>
raised it to species level again and transferred it to their newly described genus, 
<taxonomicName authority="Borovec &amp; Oberprieler, 2013" authorityName="Borovec &amp; Oberprieler" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Afrophloeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1300,1436,597,622]" italics="true" pageId="3">Afrophloeus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Borovec" box="[151,496,633,658]" pageId="3" refString="Borovec, R. &amp; Oberprieler, R. G. (2013) Afrophloeus, a new genus of African weevils of the tribe Embrithini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Entiminae), with description of a new species and notes on the composition of Embrithini. Zootaxa, 3693 (3), 365 - 378. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3693.3.7" type="journal article" year="2013">Borovec &amp; Oberprieler, 2013</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, placed in the tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="1942" box="[739,864,633,658]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Embrithini">Embrithini</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[934,1036,633,658]" pageId="3">lectotype</typeStatus>
was examined and designated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Borovec" box="[151,495,669,694]" pageId="3" refString="Borovec, R. &amp; Oberprieler, R. G. (2013) Afrophloeus, a new genus of African weevils of the tribe Embrithini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Entiminae), with description of a new species and notes on the composition of Embrithini. Zootaxa, 3693 (3), 365 - 378. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3693.3.7" type="journal article" year="2013">Borovec &amp; Oberprieler (2013)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
